- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with large scale social networks and spreading processes in these networks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a new measure and algorithmic solution to compute transmission centrality. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another possible category as the paper focuses on social networks and their dynamics. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper deals with the transmission of information in a network. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper proposes a new algorithmic solution to compute transmission centrality.
